HOUSE BILL 854
F1 6lr2268
By: Delegates Boyce and Barnes
Introduced and read first time: February 4, 2026
Assigned to: Appropriations
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 20, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 School Construction – Nonpublic Special Education School Renovation
3 Program – Established
4 FOR the purpose of establishing the Nonpublic Special Education School Renovation
5 Program in the Interagency Commission on School Construction to provide grant
6 funding to certain nonpublic special education schools for certain renovations and
7 improvements; and generally relating to the Nonpublic Special Education School
8 Renovation Program.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 5–331
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Education
17 5–331.
18 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PROGRAM” MEANS THE NONPUBLIC SPECIAL
19 EDUCATION SCHOOL RENOVATION PROGRAM.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0854*

2 HOUSE BILL 854
1 (B) (1) THERE IS A NONPUBLIC SPECIAL EDUCATION SCHOOL
2 RENOVATION PROGRAM.
3 (2) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE GRANTS TO
4 NONPUBLIC SPECIAL EDUCATION SCHOOLS FOR:
5 (I) RENOVATIONS AND IMPROVEMENTS TO CLASSROOMS AND
6 SCHOOL FACILITIES;
7 (II) UPGRADES TO RESIDENTIAL COTTAGES ON SCHOOL
8 GROUNDS THAT WILL IMPROVE STUDENT TREATMENT AND SAFETY;
9 (III) HEALTH, SAFETY, AND ACCESSIBILITY IMPROVEMENTS;
10 (IV) INFRASTRUCTURE MODERNIZATION AND TECHNOLOGY
11 UPGRADES; AND
12 (V) NEW CONSTRUCTION NECESSARY TO COMPLY WITH
13 STANDARDS SET BY THE DEPARTMENT.
14 (C) THE PROGRAM SHALL BE IMPLEMENTED AND ADMINISTERED BY THE
15 INTERAGENCY COMMISSION.
16 (D) (1) AN ELIGIBLE NONPUBLIC SPECIAL EDUCATION SCHOOL MAY
17 APPLY TO THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION TO RECEIVE A GRANT UNDER THE
18 PROGRAM.
19 (2) A NONPUBLIC SPECIAL EDUCATION SCHOOL IS ELIGIBLE FOR THE
20 PROGRAM IF THE SCHOOL:
21 (I) OPERATES IN CONJUNCTION WITH A RESIDENTIAL
22 TREATMENT CENTER THAT IS LICENSED BY THE MARYLAND DEPARTMENT OF
23 HEALTH, THE DEPARTMENT OF HUMAN SERVICES, OR THE DEPARTMENT OF
24 JUVENILE SERVICES;
25 (II) (I) PROVIDES:
26 1. HIGH SCHOOL CREDIT TOWARDS THE HIGH SCHOOL
27 GRADUATION REQUIREMENTS APPROVED BY THE DEPARTMENT; OR
28 2. A CURRICULUM AND EDUCATIONAL PROGRAM FOR
29 ELEMENTARY OR MIDDLE SCHOOL STUDENTS THAT IS APPROVED BY THE
30 DEPARTMENT; AND

HOUSE BILL 854 3
1 (III) (II) PROVIDES SERVICES FOR STUDENTS PLACED IN
2 NONPUBLIC EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS UNDER § 8–406 OF THIS ARTICLE.
3 (E) THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION MAY PRIORITIZE APPLICATIONS FOR:
4 (1) PROJECTS ADDRESSING STUDENT HEALTH OR SAFETY
5 CONCERNS;
6 (2) PROJECTS NECESSARY TO COMPLY WITH STANDARDS SET BY THE
7 DEPARTMENT; AND
8 (3) NONPUBLIC SPECIAL EDUCATION SCHOOLS WITH A HIGH
9 PERCENTAGE OF STUDENTS WHO ARE RESIDENTS OF THE STATE.
10 (F) FOR EACH FISCAL YEAR, THE GOVERNOR MAY IT IS THE INTENT OF THE
11 GENERAL ASSEMBLY THAT THE GOVERNOR INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL CAPITAL
12 BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF AT LEAST $5,000,000 TO THE PROGRAM FOR
13 EACH FISCAL YEAR.
14 (G) THE INTERAGENCY COMMISSION SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS
15 NECESSARY TO IMPLEMENT THIS SECTION.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
17 1, 2026.
Approved:
